# Component Patterns

Read `docs/guidelines/design-system.md` for visual tokens, `docs/guidelines/motion-system.md` for animation, and `docs/guidelines/surface-architecture.md` for where components sit.

## Structure

- All components use `"use client"` directive (this is a client-rendered app)
- Use `@mirohq/design-system` for buttons, icons, and basic inputs; build custom for experience-specific UI
- Co-locate types with their component; shared types go in `src/types/`
- PascalCase for components, camelCase for hooks/utilities
- Extract sub-components when a file exceeds ~200 lines

## Before You Build

1. Check existing components in `src/components/` for reusable patterns
2. Read the relevant guideline docs in `docs/guidelines/`
3. Use the glossary (`docs/guidelines/glossary.md`) for naming
